  closeButton: {fileID: 48033494}
  earthClips:
  - {fileID: 8300000, guid: 9b284a5a73233924f8d096d67ca50fe3, type: 3}
  - {fileID: 8300000, guid: 9447dd34f36f0be43b18ff2920261780, type: 3}
  - {fileID: 8300000, guid: 61c8c31fe46896544b0dfe9332e62ea2, type: 3}
  earthInfoSprite: {fileID: 21300000, guid: 9bf36bd79f7674546b081a86b78ec30a, type: 3}
  earthTexts:
  - Earth is the third planet from the Sun and the only known planet to support life.
    About 71% of its surface is covered by water.
  - It has a protective atmosphere composed mainly of nitrogen and oxygen, which
    helps regulate temperature and shield life from harmful radiation.
  - Earth rotates on its axis once every 24 hours, causing day and night, and orbits
    the Sun once every 365 days, creating the seasons.
  marsClips:
  - {fileID: 8300000, guid: 5c19dde51a6c1e248b318c261e2056bf, type: 3}
  - {fileID: 8300000, guid: 9447dd34f36f0be43b18ff2920261780, type: 3}
  - {fileID: 8300000, guid: 76c06a6f425389644a416b667df3bbed, type: 3}
  marsInfoSprite: {fileID: 21300000, guid: 49fd82bfb8454994bb4dcd9cee30c7c8, type: 3}
  marsTexts:
  - Mars is the fourth planet from the Sun and is often called the "Red Planet" because
    of its reddish appearance, caused by iron oxide (rust) on its surface.
  - It has a thin atmosphere made mostly of carbon dioxide and is much colder than
    Earth. Mars has the largest volcano in the solar system, Olympus Mons.
  - Scientists study Mars closely because it may have once had liquid water and could
    have supported microbial life in the past.
